
#package hierarchy view
To get package explorer to show the hierarchy view (vs. the flat view)
click on the \/ (right down arrow) in package explorer and open up menu
There in package presentation - select desired view

#change user name
or value of @author tag

go to eclipse.ini file and there supply user.name on command line
eclipse will read this property to set @author tag.

-vmargs
-Duser.name="rajeev jha"
-Dosgi.requiredJavaVersion=1.6

# comments for types (classes, interfaces etc.)
eclipse | windows | preferences | Java | Code style | Code templates
select comments | Types and apply.

# copyright notice to all files
install eclipse copyright plugin
Then goto
windows | preferences | general | copyright
and make changes there.

# doing error logging with java.util.Logger
Go to Menu | Run |  Run configurations
Go to Arguments tab
Go to VM arguments (and not program arguments)
Add following line to VM argument
-Djava.util.logging.config.file=/home/rjha/code/github/sensordb/java/web/logger.properties

# normal java project to Dynamic web project
This is needed to create .war files.
click on project name | properties
click project facets
select Dynamic web module

# create a .war file
click on project | export | select Web | War file
next - war file name and location

# war file - include libs

project | properties | Deployment Assembly
there you can map what all files are copied to war 






